value.value: AAC(6')-Ie-APH(2'')-Ia is an aminoglycoside acetyltransferase encoded by plasmids and transposons in S. aureus, E. faecalis, E. faecium and Staphylococcus warneri.
ANT(3'')-II-AAC(6')-IId is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside acetyltransferase in S. marcescens.
AAC(6')-30/AAC(6')-Ib' is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside acetyltransferase in P. aeruginosa.
AAC(3)-Ib/AAC(6')-Ib3 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside acetyltransferase in P. aeruginosa.
ANT(3'')-Ia is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids, transposons, integrons in Enterobacteriaceae, A. baumannii, P. aeruginosa and Vibrio cholerae.
aadA2 is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids and integrons in K. pneumoniae, Salmonella spp., Corynebacterium glutamicum, C. freundii and Aeromonas spp.
aadA3 is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids, transposons and integrons in E. coli.
aadA4 is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids and chromosomes in Bordetella parapertussis and E. coli.
aadA5 is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids, transposons and integrons in E. coli, K. pneumoniae, Kluyvera georgiana, P. aeruginosa and E. cloacae.
aadA6 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in P. aeruginosa.
aadA7 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in V. fluvialis, P. aeruginosa, E. coli, V. cholerae and S. enterica.
aadA8 is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids and integrons in V. cholerae, K. pneumoniae and Bacillus endophyticus.
aadA9 is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in C. glutamicum.
aadA11 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in E. coli and P. aeruginosa.
aadA12 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in E. coli, Yersinia enterocolitica and S. enterica.
aadA13 is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids and integrons in Pseudomonas rettgeri, P. aeruginosa, Y. enterocolitica and E. coli.
aadA14 is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in Pasteurella multocida.
aadA15 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in P. aeruginosa.
aadA16 is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids and integrons in E. coli, V. cholerae and K. pneumoniae.
aadA17 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in Aeromonas media.
aadA21 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in Salmonella spp.
aadA22 is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids and integrons in S. enterica and E. coli.
aadA23 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in S. enterica.
aadA24 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in Salmonella spp.
aadA6/aadA10 is an integron-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene cassette in P. aeruginosa.
ANT(4')-Ia is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase in S. epidermidis, S. aureus, Enterococcus spp. and Bacillus spp.
ANT(4')-IIa is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase in P. aeruginosa and Enterobacteriaceae.
ANT(4')-IIb is a transposon-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase in P. aeruginosa.

ANT(6)-Ia is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by plasmids and chromosomes in Staphylococcus epidermidis, E. faecium, Streptococcus suis, S. aureus, E. faecalis and Streptococcus mitis.
aadK is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in B. subtilis and Bacillus spp. This enzyme confers low-level resistance to streptomycin.
ANT(6)-Ia/aad(6) is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in E. faecalis and Streptococcus oralis.
ANT(6)-Ib is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene encoded by transferable pathogenicity islands in C. fetus subsp. fetus and B. subtilis.
ANT(9)-Ia is an aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase encoded by plasmids and transposons in S. aureus, Enterococcus spp., Mammaliicoccus sciuri, and E. faecalis.
spd is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside nucleotidyltransferase gene in S. aureus.
APH(2'')-Ie is a plasmid or transposon-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in E. faecium and E. casseliflavus.
APH(2'')-IIa is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in E. faecium and E. coli.
APH(2'')-IIIa is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in Enterococcus gallinarum.
APH(2'')-IVa is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in E. casseliflavus.
APH(3'')-Ia is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. griseus.
APH(3'')-Ib is an aminoglycoside phosphotransferase encoded by plasmids, transposons, integrative conjugative elements and chromosomes in Enterobacteriaceae and Pseudomonas spp.
APH(3'')-Ic is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in Mycolicibacterium fortuitum.

APH(3')-Ia is a transposon-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in E. coli and S. enterica. It is identical at the protein sequence to APH(3')-Ic, an aminoglycoside phosphotransferase encoded by plasmids, transposons and genomic islands in K. pneumoniae, A. baumannii, S. marcescens, Corynebacterium spp., Photobacterium spp. and Citrobacter spp.
APH(3')-Ib is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in E. coli.
APH(3')-IIa is a transposon-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in E. coli.
APH(3')-IIb is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in P. aeruginosa.
APH(3')-IIc is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. maltophilia.
APH(3')-IIIa is a plasmid-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in S. aureus and Enterococcus spp.
APH(3')-IVa is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in Niallia circulans.
APH(3')-Va is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in Streptomyces fradiae.
APH(3')-Vb is a chromosomal-encoded aminoglycoside phosphotransferase in Streptomyces ribosidificus.
